<TITLE> Three killed in nor'wester </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 21 (bdnews24.com)  At least three people were killed in Sherpur and Chanpainababganj when they were struck by lightning during nor'wester on Thursday and Friday. The storm also left at least 20 people injured. Saidur Rahman, 40, and wife Jotsna Begum, 35, of Rokanpur village under Gomastapur upazila, were killed in the early hours of Friday. Radhanagar Union Parishad chairman Mamunur Rashid told bdnews24.com that the couple was sleeping in the veranda when the lightning hit them. An adolescent girl was killed and at least 20 people were injured when a nor'wester swept across seven villages of the district. Over 100 houses and three mosques were damaged and a large number of trees uprooted. Local people said Sharmin Akter Rima, 15, daughter of Shaidul Islam Bhutto of Satpakia village under Sadar upazila, was struck by the lightning while she was bringing back their cattle home from the field. She was a class-X student at a local school. Of the injured, five were admitted to Jamalpur District General Hospital. Upazila Parishad chairman Ilias Uddin and Upazila Nirbahi officer M Kamal Hossain visited the storm-hit villages on Friday morning. They said loss of property is being assessed. b
